8:
How's it going, Luluca? You look a bit
stuck.
12:
How about you take a little break for
a snack?
16:
Thanks. The chief editor put me in
charge of a project targeting female
readers, but I can't come up with
a good enough idea.
19: Wow, really? What's the project about?
22:
That's the problem... I have to come up
with it myself!
27:
Uwaaaaah, Alk, I- I don't know what to
dooooo!
32:
Shh, shhh. You'll be fine.
I'll help you brainstorm, okay?
44:
I see. You're researching the "sweetest
cafes" in Palpebra? That does sound
interesting.
49:
Doesn't it? I'm targeting young female
readers like you, so I'd love to hear your
thoughts!
52:
Understood. I would be happy to help.
This certainly looks sweet.
56:
Right? I've been looking for an excuse
to come here!
61:
It definitely looks like a good find.
These smell AMAZING!
67:
Mmm! Iff's so fwuffy!
Gulpâ€” They're so sweet, too!
71:
They ARE quite fluffy.
Fluff... fluff...
75:
I wonder how they get the batter to rise
this much. They'd need some acidity...
Maybe a little touch of vinegar?
79:
This would definitely make for
a luxurious brunch date! It's GOTTA go
in the article!
83:
C'mon, let's head to the next restaurant!
It's one of my personal favorites!
88:
Huh, a-another one? I don't know if
I have room for TWO breakfasts.
92:
Honestly, me either, but I have a TON of
restaurants I need to review.
99:
We've only tried the syrup. What about
the honey? The cinnamon cream?
104:
Oh, that's a good point! The little details
might not fit into the article, but it never
hurts to research things thoroughly!
110:
All right, Stella! Let's try every
combination this place's got!
119:
Ahaha, slow down, you two. Before
you go slathering toppings over
the pancakes, let's cut them into
little taste test sized pieces.
123:
Wow, looks like it's packed again, today!
Your review was really a big hit!
127:
I looked at a few other restaurants,
but I had so much to say about each of
them, I decided to make it an ongoing
column!
129:
I'm only showcasing one at a time now,
but that gives me a lot more room for
in-depth commentary!
132:
I think detailed articles are easier to
understand than little summaries.
135: Yeah! That's what I was thinking too!
140:
Well, looks like you were right! I'm
looking forward to the next issue
already!
146:
Thanks! I've got another great review
in the works!
150:
It looks like we'll have to go somewhere
else for brunch today though.
My fluffy pancakes...
153:
It'd be dinner by the time we got a table,
huh? Guess we'll have to whip up some
pancakes ourselves!
157:
Let's swing by the grocery and head
back to Starview. Does that work for
you, Luluca?
166:
It's a shame you don't have a restaurant
to review, Alk. You'd have the whole city
lined up!
